<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870629-0073 </DOCNO><HL> Harsco Division Gets$103.2 Million AwardFor Trucks to Army</HL><DD> 06/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HSC IBM GE MD NPH HPC WX RTNDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The BMY division of Harsco Corp. received $103.2 million in Army contracts to produce five-ton trucks.    International Business Machines Corp. was awarded an $81.5 million Navy contract for spare parts for shipboard weapon-control systems.    General Electric Co. won a $49 million Air Force contract for ballistic missile reentry vehicle equipment.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was issued $45.6 million in Air Force contracts for F15 aircraft radar improvements and engineering services.    Magnavox Electronic Systems Co., a unit of North American Philips Corp., received a $35.5 million Air Force contract for aircraft communications equipment.    Hercules Inc. was awarded a $23.2 million Navy contract for Sparrow missile rocket motors.    Purdy Corp. was issued a $16 million Army contract for UH-60 helicopter equipment.    Hazeltine Corp. won a $13.6 million Navy contract for communications equipment for P-3 and S-3 aircraft.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. received a $10.2 million Air Force contract for E-3A aircraft radar parts.    Raytheon Co. received a $10 million Navy contract for Tartar missile engineering services. </TEXT></DOC>